{{ja-pos|proper|гӮҸ}}

# {{lb|ja|historical|derogatory}} [[ancient]] [[Japan]]

====Usage notes====
During the Nara period, Japanese scholars believed that {{lang|ja|еҖӯ}} was derogatory as a name for their own country, because the Chinese word depicted a man bending down. Around 757 {{CE}}, Japan replaced {{lang|ja|еҖӯ}} with {{ja-r|е’Ң|^гӮҸ}}, which had the same pronunciation in Old Japanese, but instead meant "harmonious".

